boroughs_grouped = boroughs.groupby('Borough', as_index=False)[['Income']].mean()
In [6]:
boroughs_grouped['Income'] = boroughs_grouped['Income'].round()
boroughs_grouped['Income'] = boroughs_grouped['Income'].astype(int)

Loop through and find coordinates for each borough

In [8]:
latitude=[] #List to collect the latitudes
longitude=[] #List to collect the longitudes

geolocator = Nominatim()

for address in boroughs_grouped['Borough']: #Iterate through 'Borough' to collect the locations data
    location = geolocator.geocode(address)
    latitude.append(location.latitude)
    longitude.append(location.longitude)
    

boroughs_grouped['Latitude']=latitude #Add Latitude column into original dataframe 

boroughs_grouped['Longitude']=longitude #Add Longitude column into original dataframe
boroughs_grouped

In [10]:
# create map of New York using latitude and longitude values
map_newyork = folium.Map(location=[latitude, longitude], zoom_start=10)

# add markers to map
for lat, lng, borough, income in zip(boroughs_grouped['Latitude'], boroughs_grouped['Longitude'], boroughs_grouped['Borough'], boroughs_grouped['Income']):
    label = '{}, {}'.format(borough, income)
    label = folium.Popup(label, parse_html=True)
    folium.CircleMarker(
        [lat, lng],
        radius=5,
        popup=label,
        color='blue',
        fill=True,
        fill_color='#3186cc',
        fill_opacity=0.7,
        parse_html=False).add_to(map_newyork)  
    
map_newyork
